atoms.source_snippet:
/// to validate whether they fit into the pool or not. Default is 2 times [`TX_SLOT_BYTE_SIZE`],
/// which defaults to 32 KiB, so 64 KiB. Can be overridden with the `RETH_MAX_TX_INPUT_BYTES`
/// environment variable.
pub const DEFAULT_MAX_TX_INPUT_BYTES: usize = 2 * TX_SLOT_BYTE_SIZE; // 64KB

destinations.snippet:
/// [`TX_SLOT_BYTE_SIZE`] is used to calculate how many data slots a single transaction
/// takes up based on its byte size. The slots are used as `DoS` protection, ensuring
/// that validating a new transaction remains a constant operation (in reality
/// O(maxslots), where max slots are 4 currently).
pub const TX_SLOT_BYTE_SIZE: usize = 32 * 1024;
